  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Environmental monitoring and management and alternative development in Canapia and Salado basins</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project continues the work of PER303, emphasising advocacy to generate environmental policies in Espinar&apos;s environmental agenda, the prioritisation of development alternatives in both watersheds and rescheduling of activities it was not possible to carry out under PER303 due to the global pandemic. This project also prioritises institutional strengthening through coordinated interventions with strategic allies, and capacity strengthening to influence political actors during the political elections in 2021. The main project participants are the promoters, environmental defenders and community leaders who will receive training to influence the establishment of environmental policies and proposals for development and to share these examples more widely. The project will include exchanges with other communities on alternative development.</narrative>
  </description>
